title.narrative: Progress towards malaria elimination in Solomon Islands

description.narrative: Solomon Islands - Malaria - Solomon Islands Ministry of Health and Medical Services - MHMS. This program has the following goals: By the end of 2021 elimination-ready surveillance will be fully developed and operational in all low burden provinces and then expanded in phases to cover all provinces by 2025.. By 2025 the national API will be reduced to pre-2015 levels of 30 per thousand and at least three provinces will have reached zero indigenous cases.. By the end of 2030 there will be zero indigenous cases of malaria.. By the end of 2034 the Country will be certified malaria free.. The objectives of this program are: To maintain high LLIN coverage, increase usage and carry out targeted IRS to bring down malaria cases in high burden areas.. To maximize access to and utilisation of early laboratory confirmed diagnosis and appropriate treatment for malaria.. To maximize program impact through partnership and improved financial management. To achieve elimination criteria in pre-elimination provinces and reach and maintain API <1/1,000 in provinces already designated for elimination (Choiseul and Isabel). To move towards malaria elimination (in-line with the governmentâ€™s commitment to national elimination by 2035).. To support the Ministry of Health in strengthening health systems nationwide.
